                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAANL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The measurement was performed using",
                "the ATLAS facility at Argonne National Laboratory."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "CD2 target with thickness of 150 mu-g/cm2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three annular double-sided silicon strip",
                "detectors were used for the detection of the protons",
                "at backward angles between 110deg and 161deg in the",
                "laboratory system.The DSSDs  with thicknesses of",
                "500 mu-m each, were segmented into 16 annular rings on",
                "the front and 16 azimuthal wedges on the back."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The recoiling B ions (11,12,13B)",
                "were detected in a telescope of dE-E silicon",
                "detectors segmented into four quadrants covering the",
                "forward angle range of 1.3deg to 7.2deg in the",
                "laboratory system. The forward telescope detector",
                "consisted of a 75 mu-m thick dE detector and",
                "a 1000 mu-m E detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between forward and backward",
                "detectors was required"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "12B beam was produced using the in-flight method via",
                "the (d,p) reaction, by bombarding a deuterium gas cell",
                "with an 81-MeV primary 11B beam with an intensity of",
                "approximately 100 pnA. The resulting 12B beam had an",
                "energy of 75 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "From charged particle reactions the branching ratio of",
                "the neutron-unbound state at Eex=3.389MeV was measured.",
                "From this, ratio of partial widths Gn/Gg and reaction",
                "rates for 11,12B(n,g) were obtained."
              ]
            }
          ],
